description: There is no story let alone a plot summary to this issue. It is PURELY a book of PIN-UP IMAGES.

Includes Previews of:

  • Ultimate Comics Captain America #1
  • Thanos Imperative: Devastation #1
  • Namor: The First Mutant #6
  • Captain America: Hail HYDRA #1
  • Daredevil Reborn #1
  • X-Men #7
  • Wolverine & Jubilee #1
name: One Shot

description: In the aftermath of the battle with Hela, the team is in upheaval. One member leaves...another arrives...Rictor and Rahne finally have it out over the identity of her baby's father. Guaranteed to be the most emotional issue of X-Factor this month!
name: Keeping Things

description: Paradoxx has banished Delta-Void from the Continuum because he failed to defeat Nira-X time and time again. Wreaking havoc in Mecha New York, Delta-Void soon encounters Nira-X. Again, Nira-X defeats him.
name: Delta-Void the destroyer

description: Based on the all-new animated series! Join CLIFFJUMPER and ARCEE as they battle their way through DECEPTICON forces in a desperate adventure to learn the secrets of Space Bridge Technology! STARSCREAM, the DECEPTICON enforcer stands in their way, not just from the mission, but to rejoin OPTIMUS PRIME and his AUTOBOTS as well! This is the PREQUEL to the new hit TV Show!

In the year 2192, three villains (Delta-Void, Millenia and Quid) escape the timestream by going through a plasma-gate, set in a government science facility in New York. Nira-X, now able to travel through time, encounters the villains, but is defeated. The three villains revive Paradoxx, before Nira-X gets a second chance to fight them. Delta-Void shoots randomly, hitting the main control systems. With the timelink out of control, the time-gate opens and Nira-X, Paradoxx and the villains are pulled through.

In 1995, Nira-X encounters her counterpart, who reveals she has hidden the time-element in a starbird which is set to appear in Central Park. With the time-element, Paradoxx would be able to rewrite history into his own image.

Paradoxx steals the time-element from the ship's crew. Nira-X joins the ship's crew, fighting back against Paradoxx and his gang. Nira-X shoots the time-element, saves the universe and everybody is returned to their own present-day reality. Nira-X awakes in a place between Heaven and Hell, called Continuum, where she's greeted by Kathryn.

Instead of having returned to their own reality, Paradoxx and his gang have returned to New York City, though slightly altered. Millenia meets her counterpart.

Nira-X is under great scrutiny by Kathryn, who thinks Nira is detined to lead Paradoxx to victory. Nira escapes and follows Paradoxx again to New York City. It seems that Paradoxx plans to blow up the city by sealing the underground water conduits, overheating the power stations.

Nira-X foils Paradoxx' plan to blow up the city. In the end, she even comes face-to-face with him. Making sure that Paradoxx doesn't contain any more parts of her brother, she kills Paradoxx by blowing a big hole in his chest. Kathryn finds Nira-X sitting next to Paradoxx' body. Kathryn's doubt about Nira is taken away and she makes her a Cyberangel.
Nira-X travels to the future to save her younger self from Delta-Void and Millenia.
The Director of Oasis returns from limbo, Dunkan turns traitor and Nira-X meets another Cyberangel, called Mercy.
name: New foe, old friend

description: Nira-X discovers the true nature of her cyberskin, makes friends with the other cyberangels and deals with the Director once and for all.
name: New friends, eternal enemies

description: Nira-X travels to the 10th century to fight against a real dragon.
After defeating Oasis, Nira needs to secure the last known facility of Oasis in Mecha New York. But the former agents of Oasis plan on taking the facility as their own.
name: California girl back in Mecha

description: Can Nira-X and her sometimes partner police officer Mac Elrok keep Cyberhood out of government clutches? Will Cyberhood get revenge on an old enemy who experimented on children? Not if the FBI has something to say about it.

Cruising past an island, Nira-X and Kathryn witness an explosion on the island. Investigating it, Nira-X and Kathryn encounter Dragon-Man who is on the run for Oasis shock troopers and Nira-X's old enemies, Delta-Void and Millenia.
name: Eye of the storm (part 1)

description: Kathryn and Nira-X are captured by Oasis. While Nira-X is experimented on by the Director, Kathryn is locked up with Dragon-Man. The device on Dragon-Man's back keeps his wings in check. Knowing their technology, Kathryn is able to undo the device. Now able to fly, Dragon-Man breaks out of his prison, taking Kathryn and Nira-X with him.
name: Eye of the storm, part 2

description: Kathryn and Nira rendez-vous with former Oasis scientist Dunkan Riley, who is escorted by Mac Elrok. Together with Dragon-Man they re-enter the Oasis facility on the Carribean island, trying to stop the Director from going back in time and rewriting history to fit his own goals. Unable to stop him, the Director enters a time-gate and steps through. However, Dunkan has secretly recoded all the key systems. As a result, the Director did not go back in time, he sent himself to limbo instead. Stealing the only vehicle of Oasis left that is capable of time-travel, Nira-X, Kathryn and Dunkan return Dragon-Man and Mac Elrok to their own place before setting off.
name: Eye of the storm, part 3

description: Abducted by aliens, both Nira-X and Cynder are taken to planet Lofkan, once the home of a great Olympic arena where, 1000 years ago, over 14 civilized worlds competed in. Since then, it disintegrated into a cesspool where abducted warriors battle solely for the entertainment of the emperor Janus Kor Prime. Mentally influenced by the emperor, Nira-X and Cynder battle each other in the arena. When the emperor shifts his control to a nearby dragon, Nira-X and Cynder break free from the mental control and use the dragon to hurl the emperor from his pilar to his death below. Having beaten the tournament, Nira and Cynder are allowed to leave.

Unsure wether to accept a new mission from Kathryn or not, Nira-X goes out crimehunting by herself. She hears a scream and checks it out. It turns out that the alien Death-Skorn has crashlanded on Earth.
name: Heatwave

description:
After regaining consciousness, Nira-X sets out to find Death-Skorn. Finding him, she secretly plants a bomb on the back of his head. This knocks him out and Death-Skorn is hauled away in a police containment vehicle.

The Director of Oasis visits Kathryn with the promise of promotion, if only she kills Nira-X.
name: Prime target

description: Death-Skorn escapes from his temporary confinement and faces off against Nira-X and Officer Elrok. Meanwhile, the Director of Oasis reveals his true nature to Kathryn.
name: Invasions, decisions

description: Though outnumbered, Nira-X and Officer Elrok stand their ground against the five alien criminals. When Oasis shock troopers arrive, Nira-X thinks they are on her side. She is surprised to discover they're not. The shock troopers defeat and deport the aliens. Kathryn shows up and fakes her and Nira-X's death. Secretly, they intend to lay low for a while while drifting on a yacht in the Carribean.
name: Unfinished business

description: When the embodiment of dark, Deathgate, escapes from his prison, it is up to Hellina and Nira-X to stop him. But will they survive Hell to do it?
Nira-X, Cyberhood and Mac Elrok take on Arnold Linquest and his lackeys. Who will win? Also, more information on the background of the enigmatic Cyberhood.
While Cyberhood and Mac Elrok confront the last surivor of the aliens on board of the spaceship, Nira-X is jumped by Delta-Void. Also, the return of Kathryn Styles!
Nira-X faces her brother Paradoxx in the continuum. Fighting alongside other Cyberangels, will Nira-X be able to defeat her brother again?

name: Dr Sex in het Oostblok

description: Who â or what â are The Puzzlemen? Ancient artifacts are being stolen from museums around the world. So far, there seems to be little significance to their individual potential power. Put the puzzle together, though, and the All-Stars are up against a threat that endangers more than just all of humanity! Meanwhile, Roxy gets schooled in compassion by a Justice Society member from the past!
name: The Puzzlemen, Part 1: Appassionato

description:
Don't miss this prequel to the acclaimed graphic novel by Warren Ellis and Cully Hamner. Paul Moses was a killer in the service of the C.I.A. for decades and has the nightmares to prove it. But what mission was the turning point to his retirement? What betrayal cut so deep that it went all the way to the top?

Paul Moses is a man plagued by his deeds as a professional killer for the CIA. "Eyes Only" covers the story of just how Paul came to retire from service.

It's the holidays and Rex is thinking about familyâ¦or his lack thereof. But there's no time for melancholy when Biowulf attacks! Also, Ben 10 is bound and determined to get the season's hottest video game â and no one and nothing will stop him!
name: Give & Get; Home For the Holidays; Operation: E.G.G.N.O.G.; Gift of the Samurai

description: It's been two years since the apocalypse. The zombie plague has (mostly) died down, but the world that remains is still a very dangerous place. Dr. Ian Scott continues to brave it all as he travels from Colorado to West Virginia with two vital goals: deliver a potential zombie vaccine and find the woman he loves, if she isn't deadâor undead.
name: Dead New World

description: This is a preview for a new superman.

With the prom just around the corner, Megamind hatches a plan to usurp the imminent prom king, Metro Dude, but when his dastardly deed takes a self-destructive turn, heâs forced to challenge his teenaged nemesis to a dance off in front of the entire class, ultimately usurping himself.
name: Can I Have This Dance; Minion, Where's The Car?; Minion's Day Off, Part 1

description: Stranded in Brazil, Skipper enlists the help of some unusual locales, including a snake named Jose who is anything but, in order to reunite his dispersed team of penguin paratroopers, but will the mission diversion keep them from completing their original objective of returning Mia, the duck-billed platypus, to her native home of Australia? Â  Â
name: Operation: Wonder From Down Under! Part 2 of 4; Operation: Birthday Blowout; Petey the Pestilence! Part 2 of 4

description: When Shrek, Donkey, and Puss embark on a guy's weekend of camping and male bonding, they unknowingly pitch their tent in the middle of a haunted forest, trading marshmallows and graham crackers for ghosts and goblins. But as the scares mount, something is not quite what it seems, forcing the trio to face their fears head on!
name: Buddies Night Out; Attack of the Pants Phantoms! Part 2 of 4; Dentist For the Dronkeys; Bedtime Story

description:
Just after going through a wormhole, Zen's ship is attacked by a Rygulian spaceship. Shooting back, the Rygulians crash down on the nearby planet. Zen follows the Rygulians to their crashsite. Zen encounters the Rygulian pilot, and learns the fight between them was based on a malfunction on the part of the Rygulians. Before they can form a bond, Zen and the Rygulian are attacked by Paradoxx, who has escaped from his time-loop.

The alien race called Gordons hire Nira-X as their mercenary to stop Paradoxx.

Nira-X and Zen fight Paradoxx, but they are no match for him.

Backup story: Wanting to learn about his past, a young Zen travels to the mountain top to meditate. There he finds a woman, bound to the rocks.
name: Welcome to Alternity
